decision_conditions:
Condition : 8 - The illuminated advertisement hereby approved shall comply with the following terms:
	
(a)	The intensity of the illumination of the building-mounted signs (east, south, west and north) shall not exceed 550 cd/m2;
(b)	The intensity of the illumination of the flagpole shall not exceed 580 cd/m2;
(c)    The intensity of the illumination of the poster display unit shall not exceed 225 cd/m2;
(d)    The intensity of the illumination of the billboard shall not exceed 500 cd/m2;
(e)	The advertisement shall be fitted with a light intensity monitoring censor to ensure the illuminance intensity is dimmable to take account of ambient light conditions and comply with the maximum recommended lighting intensity; 
(f)	The advertisement shall not display any moving, or apparently moving, images; 

Reason: In the interests of amenity and highway safety.
